XIN_illegitimate_regime_desc.value: The Xin Dynasty was established by an impostor, a conspirator behind the Han's order. While he might have taken the power in China, underground agents and resistance cells still exist, and many would prefer to see the come back of the Han Dynasty, than continue to see Wang Mang and his policies.

XIN_peasant_support_fading_desc.value: The current regime is beginning to lose support from the peasants, which were the ones to put the Xin Dynasty on the throne. This might be problematic in the future, especially if the situation worsens.

XIN_unsustainable_army_desc.value: We mobilised so much to defend against the Xiongnu in the north and the rebels in the south, but we cannot keep that many soldiers in line without consequences.

XIN_poor_sino_xiongnu_relations_desc.value: Our relations with the Xiongnu are very low. If we continue, they might chose to attack us.

PTH_decentralised_structure_desc.value: Our Empire is vast and wide, and to keep in check these numerous regions, we are forced to adopt a decentralised approach, guaranting stability in the realm. This however results in some satraps wanting to break free from us.

XAI_poor_sino_xiongnu_relations_desc.value: Our relations with the Chinese are very low. If they don't want to talk or trade with us, we'll need to intervene.

pax_romana_desc.value: Established by Augustus following the restoration of our Republic, the Pax Romana stabilised our nation and mmakes us feared by other states.

ROE_restricted_citizenship_desc.value: Even if we extended the roman citizenship to many cities, there is still so many people that are not rightful citizens of Rome. We must either allow them to participate in roman affairs, or force them into submission.

one_party_monopoly_desc.value: Rome's supremacy over the Empire is a powerful symbol. Whoever controls Rome controls the Empire, and everything with it. RLosing Rome would mean losing everything.!

nomadic_society_desc.value: We are no State, we are no defined lands, we are Peoples, peoples travelling the steppes and moving. We aren't stable, we aren't 'controllable', we are free. Such is the way of living, in a nomadic society.

dam_desc.value: Dams provide additional power to a state, improving industry and resource output.

canal_kiel_desc.value: The Kiel Canal Locks are needed in place in order for the canal to operate at full capacity, and destroying them would hinder shipping and movement for a long time.

canal_panama_desc.value: The Panama Canal Locks are needed in place in order for the canal to operate at full capacity, and destroying them would hinder shipping and movement for a long time.

industrial_complex_desc.value: This building provides the state with industry for production of civilian goods or construction of new buildings. Can be converted to military industry if needed.

radar_station_desc.value:
Radar allows you to gain intel on enemy troops in nearby states.
A higher radar level in a state increases the effective range of the radar.
Radar also provides the state with better detection of enemy air forces, giving your planes a better chance to engage them.
In addition radar increases the detection of enemy fleets at sea.

nuclear_reactor_heavy_water_desc.value: This building provides the state with production of enriched Uranium for use in Nuclear weapons.\nNuclear reactors using Heavy Water are somewhat cheaper to build than Graphite Reactors, but produce less material that can be used to produce nuclear weapons.

nuclear_reactor_desc.value: This building provides the state with production of enriched Uranium for use in Nuclear weapons.

nuclear_facility_desc.value: Experimental Facilities for Nuclear Research allow you to start research projects relating to the use nuclear power.

air_facility_desc.value: Experimental Facilities for Aerodynamics and Avionics allow you to start research projects for aircraft, rockets and related electronics.

naval_facility_desc.value: Experimental Facilities for Naval Engineering allow you to start research projects related to Surface Ships and Submarines.\nA Naval Engineering can only be created in a coastal province.

mega_gun_emplacement_desc.value: Operating on the principle of multi-charge propulsion, this large caliber gun is designed to achieve unparalleled ranges in bombardment. Utilizing a series of underground tunnels, it accelerates shells to supersonic speeds before launching them towards distant targets.

stronghold_network_desc.value: An extensive defensive system of massive bunkers and strongly fortified positions, designed to repel enemy advances and secure key strategic areas.

land_facility_desc.value: Experimental Facilities for Land Warfare  allow you to start research projects related to various aspects of land warfare, such as special tanks, or artillery.

landmark_statue_of_liberty_desc.value: The colossal Statue of Liberty stands proudly in New York Harbor, a major entry point to the United States for immigrants looking to start a new life. Subsequently, it has come to embody the American ethos of life, liberty and the pursuit of happiness.

landmark_big_ben_desc.value: The Westminster Clock Tower, more commonly known as Big Ben, is a British cultural icon. It is one of the most prominent symbols of the United Kingdom and parliamentary democracy. It was originally completed in 1859 in a Gothic Revival style, and is the third tallest tower in Great Britain.

landmark_colosseum_desc.value: The Colosseum lies in the center of Rome. It is the largest ancient amphitheater ever built, being used by the Romans, and the people of the city following the downfall of the Romans, for entertainment ever since it's completion by Emperor Titus.

landmark_cristo_redentor_desc.value: Christ the Redeemer towers over Rio de Janeiro, with its construction being finished in 1931. It is a national symbol of Brazil, and holds great importance among the Catholics in the region.

landmark_eiffel_tower_desc.value: The Eiffel Tower is named after its creator Gustave Eiffel, and was finished in 1889. Being located on the Champ de Mars in Paris, the Iron Lady has become a global cultural icon of France, and is a symbol of national pride.

landmark_kremlin_desc.value: The Moscow Kremlin is a fortified complex. Within the complex is the Grand Kremlin Palace, which served as the royal residence of the Emperor of Russia. The Kremlin overlooks the Moskva River to the south, Saint Basil's Cathedral and Red Square to the east, and Alexander Garden to the west. Nowadays it has come to represent the authority of the state and it's control over the people.

landmark_berlin_reichstag_desc.value: The Plenarbereich Reichstagsgebude, also known as the Reichstag, is a historic legislative government building on Platz der Republik in Berlin. Up until the Reichstag fire of 1933 it was used by the federal council in Germany, but even so it is a symbolic building that holds great importance in the hearts and minds of the people.

landmark_hofburg_palace_desc.value: The Hofburg is the former principal imperial palace of the Habsburg dynasty, and faces towards the Heldenplatz. Maybe one day, the palace can once again be used by the rulers of Austria, be it a president or a king.

landmark_berlin_volkshalle_desc.value: The Volkshalle stands as a testament to our people's indomitable spirit, and their prideful will to dominate the globe. It will show the world that, through the might of conquest, anything is possible, and the fatherland can make even the most impossible task possible.

landmark_sadabad_complex_desc.value: Built by the Qajars and expanded by the Pahlavis, the Sa'dabad Complex in northern Tehran serves as a royal residence and seat of power. Its palaces and gardens reflect Irans shifting political landscape, from conservatism to modernism.

landmark_taj_mahal_desc.value: The Taj Mahal stands as a masterpiece of Mughal architecture. Its grand white marble domes and intricate gardens make it one of the most iconic symbols of India, a testament to both imperial power and enduring legacy.

landmark_hagia_sophia_desc.value: Standing at the crossroads of empires, the Hagia Sophia has been a Byzantine cathedral, an Ottoman mosque, and a symbol of Istanbuls ever-changing rulers. Its massive dome and grand halls reflect both its spiritual significance and the ambitions of those who claimed the city as their own.

doctrine_effort_2_desc.value: The battlefield has changed not just in the interbellum years, but over the course of recent conflicts. We must continuously reevaluate our doctrines to reflect this.

equipment_effort_3_desc.value: Instead of imitating or buying foreign equipment, we should aim to become world-leading in infantry weapons.

armor_effort_desc.value: Applying what we have learned from mechanizing our infantry, we can improve our armored vehicles as well.

special_forces_desc.value: We have need of elite forces; mountain troops and paratroopers should be our priority.

aviation_effort_tt.value: Not enough building slots for YAir Base!

aviation_effort_desc.value: Nowhere is technological advances more rapid than in aerial warfare. Aviation is a field any modern nation must master.

fighter_focus_desc.value: We have not seen that last of dogfights in the Great War. Keeping ahead in the development of fighter planes will give us an edge in the future.

bomber_focus_desc.value: When people of the future speak of the horror to today's wars, fire raining from the skies will prominently feature. We will do our best to ensure those stories are told by our enemies.

aviation_effort_2_desc.value: Further advances in aviation will be necessary to integrate our air force well with other branches of the military.

CAS_effort_desc.value: A modern army needs support from vehicles not only on the ground, but also in the air.

rocket_effort_desc.value: Rocket and jet engines allow for unprecedented speeds for unmanned and manned vessels alike. Pioneering these technologies will allow us to take the enemy by surprise.

NAV_effort_desc.value: Just as the new naval warfare takes place in part beneath the water's surface, part of it takes place in the air above the waters.

naval_effort_tt.value: Not enough building slots for YNaval Dockyards!

naval_effort_desc.value: The expansion of our navy should be our first priority. Assign all available resources to new Dockyards and research into light surface ships.

flexible_navy_desc.value: Reinventing naval warfare to account for the advances in submarine technology will allow us to strike efficiently against enemy convoys.

large_navy_desc.value: Adapting our naval doctrines to accommodate large ships and ensuring the safety of our trade convoys will teach us much about what sort of ships we need.

submarine_effort_desc.value: Submarine warfare is the most exciting naval development since the invention of the torpedo boat. We would do well to not just protect against submarines, but also use them against enemy shipping.

cruiser_effort_desc.value: Before making forays into advanced battleship research, the smaller cruisers are in need of replacement.

destroyer_effort_desc.value: Studying the design and strategic use of submarines, we have also learned how to counter those strategies. Destroyers will be crucial for this.

capital_ships_effort_desc.value: The nation with the most battleships will rule the oceans. Battleships and carriers represent the old and the new in naval superiority.

industrial_effort_desc.value: Focus all our political efforts on building up the civilian industry in a great leap forward.

industrial_effort_2_desc.value: With iron will and a relentless work ethic, we can mobilize the people in another great industrial effort.

construction_effort_tt.value: Not enough building slots for YCivilian Factories!

construction_effort_desc.value: Civilian industrial capacity must not be underestimated even when war looms over the world.

production_effort_tt.value: Not enough building slots for YMilitary Factory!

production_effort_desc.value: If you can build tractors, you can build tanks! We must not allow our military production capacity to lag behind.

construction_effort_2_desc.value: Continuing to expand our factories will allow us to speed up production of goods for trade and further construction efforts.

production_effort_2_desc.value: Trying to adapt civilian factories to produce military equipment is inefficient. We should focus on preparing military production now.

production_effort_3_desc.value: Continued efforts to expand our military factories are necessary to meet the demands for new equipment.

infrastructure_effort_desc.value: A country without proper infrastructure cannot pursue advanced projects or constructions.

infrastructure_effort_tt.value: Not enough building slots for YInfrastructure!

synth_oil_effort_tt.value: Not enough building slots for YSynthetic Refinery!

infrastructure_effort_2_desc.value: Extending our infrastructure further will enable the transports and communications necessary for high-tech clandestine projects.

construction_effort_3_desc.value: Expansion of our infrastructure network has significantly improved our capacity for construction.

nuclear_effort_desc.value: Standing on the edge of a world-changing discovery, we cannot let others light the fire that may one day consume the Earth.

extra_tech_slot_desc.value: Our industrial expansion and other recent advances might allow us to conduct more R&D in parallel.

extra_tech_slot_2_desc.value: The rapid industrialization of our nation has opened up new opportunities in R&D that we should pursue.

technology_sharing_desc.value: By sharing technological advances with our allies, our whole faction will be able to conduct wartime R&D more efficiently.

secret_weapons_desc.value: It is tempting to expend all extra resources into developing tanks and planes, but the secret to winning wars lies in whole new fields of science; electronics, rocketry and nuclear research.

political_effort_desc.value: To bring about change in the world, we need to be able to bring about change in our own country. Strengthening our political position should come first.

collectivist_ethos_desc.value: Our enemies may divide and conquer lesser nations, but our people will stand united. All for one and one for all.

liberty_ethos_desc.value: In this time of ideological fanatics who seek to suffocate the human spirit, we will safeguard individual liberties and freedom.

militarism_desc.value: Those who view the military as a necessary evil are doomed to hesitate in the face of war. We will ingrain militarism into our culture to become a people of soldiers.

political_correctness_desc.value: People holding mildly controversial or otherwise embarrassing opinions appear to be concerned that there is a wide-reaching conspiracy against them. This seems like an excellent idea.

neutrality_focus_desc.value: While others may claim it takes bravery and wisdom to take sides in a global conflict, we know it takes more to refuse.

interventionism_focus_desc.value: We value the freedom of all people, not only our own citizens. If preventing tyranny means war, then so be it.

military_youth_desc.value: Organizations to promote discipline and political education of young people in our nation will foster loyalty and self-sacrifice early.

deterrence_desc.value: Standing alone, we rarely benefit from war. Fortunately, we know that the best defense is one so well-known you never have to put it to use.

volunteer_corps_desc.value: Forcing our people to die for ideals of freedom would be an exercise in irony, but establishing means for those who wish to aid people abroad is not.

paramilitarism_desc.value: Military principles have applications outside of the military. With the development of semi-militarized units to complement our armed forces, more people will have military training.

indoctrination_focus_desc.value: Having established our ideology as based on the truth, it may be taught as truth. Education and media must reflect this lesson.

foreign_expeditions_desc.value: With our enemies prepared to intervene in distant conflicts on behalf of their ideals, we must be ready to do the same for ours.

why_we_fight_effect.value: If we don't have the YNeutral Foreign Policy! spirit we will be able to create factions.\n

why_we_fight_desc.value: The world is growing increasingly unsafe. Our people need to see the atrocities being committed by those who crave power. It is time we rally the people to our cause and ensure everyone is ready to fight for our freedom.

political_commissars_desc.value: To ensure that our policies are followed in military practice, we will introduce politically appointed officials into military ranks.

internationalism_focus_desc.value: Ideology knows no borders. Another nation may call itself sovereign, but our convictions are above such claims.

nationalism_focus_desc.value: Our nation is unique, and our political achievements could only have happened here. We must fight for it at any cost.

ideological_fanaticism_desc.value: Our politically established values and goals are worth dying for as much as any ancient faith. Any follower should be prepared to face death, and those who stray better be prepared to face death.

air_innovation_desc.value: Modern wars cannot be won without dominating the skies. We must do everything in our power to develop the air force!

air_innovation_2_desc.value: Every advantage we can gain in the skies is precious. We should focus all of our efforts on developing our fighters.

naval_air_effort_desc.value: The efficacy of air strikes against naval targets was demonstrated by the Americans already back in 1921. We should not neglect this branch of the Air Force if we intend to wage war on a naval power.

ROE_first_roman_emperor.value: The First Emperor of the Romans

submarine_desc.value: Submarines employ stealth and powerful torpedoes to destroy enemy convoys.

both_cruisers_desc.value: Light Cruiser - A light screening vessel. Its primary duty is to shield capital ships from enemy light ships but can also unleash powerful torpedoes that can hurt bigger ships.\n\nHeavy Crusier - A large armored cruiser that is pretty flexible. A good choice for nations who can't afford to build larger capital ships.

light_cruiser_desc.value: A light screening vessel. Its primary duty is to shield capital ships from enemy light ships but can also unleash powerful torpedoes that can hurt bigger ships.

heavy_cruiser_desc.value: A large armored cruiser that is pretty flexible. A good choice for nations who can't afford to build larger capital ships.

destroyer_desc.value: The lightest screening vessel. Its job is to defend larger ships and to find and destroy submarines.

ship_hull_light_desc.value: The lightest screening vessel. Its job is to defend larger ships and to find and destroy submarines.

carrier_desc.value: A capital ship able to carry wings of powerful carrier capable aircraft into battle. Also useful as a floating airfield you can position off the coast of your enemy.

battleship_desc.value: The largest capital ship with the biggest guns and strongest armor that money can buy. Such an expensive investment deserves proper support of smaller screening ships.

armor_desc.value: The largest and strongest armor that money can buy.

battle_cruiser_desc.value: A large capital ship often with offensive abilities close to those of a battleship, but with weaker armor traded for a faster speed.

convoy_desc.value: Convoys used for international trade of goods and resources. Also used to ferry troops around and for performing naval invasions.

sh_battleship_desc.value: The largest capital ship with the biggest guns and strongest armor that money can buy. Such an expensive investment deserves proper support of smaller screening ships.

JET_ENGINES_SPECIAL.value: The development of Jet Engines is an essential prerequisite for the development of jet powered aircraft. This must be researched before you can research advanced aircraft

jet_engines_desc.value: A breakthrough in propulsion technology, the Jet Engine will enable the development of an entirely new generation of aircraft.

armored_car_equipment_desc.value: Light-weight armored wheeled vehicles. Common for reconnaissance and resistance suppression, but can be fitted with heavier armaments.

motorized_equipment_desc.value: Trucks used for transporting troops, supplies, and for division motorization.

motorized_equipment_0_desc.value: During the Great War the armies starting using basic civilian trucks for transporting supplies and hauling equipment. These have since become an integral part of most armies.

motorized_equipment_1_desc.value: Motorizing infantry is the first stage towards the mechanization of an army. Civilian trucks are readily adaptable to military uses of transporting soldiers, towing guns, and carrying equipment and supplies. This greatly increases the strategic mobility of infantry units, which would otherwise rely on marching.

support_equipment_desc.value: Radios, Jeeps, Pontoons & other equipment used to support troops.

support_equipment_1_desc.value: Radios, Jeeps, Pontoons & other equipment used to support troops.
